  "text": "The algorithm proposed by Guimera and Amaral [CITATION_1] (or GA for short) also tries to find a partition of a network with the maximum modularity. However, different from FN, GA adopts simulated annealing (SA) to regulate the local search process in order to obtain a better solution. Similar to KL, starting from an initial partition of a network, GA generates, evaluates, accepts or rejects a new neighbor partition from the current one in each iteration. To generate a new neighbor partition, GA moves or swaps nodes between groups, divides a group or merges two groups. Then GA evaluates the new partition by calculating its modularity and decides whether or not to accept it by using the metropolis criterion given in Eq.2 based on the current system temperature.",
